{
  "texts": [
    "During training, the weights and biases of the autoencoder are adjusted to minimize the reconstruction error using an optimization algorithm like stochastic gradient descent.",
    "Once trained, the encoding function can create low-dimensional representations of new input data (Z), while the decoding function can reconstruct the original data from the low-dimensional representation (X ′).",
    "Traditional AE typically employs a single-layer encoder, making it challenging to extract deep features.",
    "To enhance feature extraction, one effective strategy is to deepen the neural network structure.",
    "By employing a layer-wise learning approach, multiple basic autoencoders can be stacked together to form a Stacked Autoencoder (SAE), allowing for the extraction of complex data features."
  ]
}